"I'm more interested in getting it right, than being right"....dave


On Thu, 14 Feb 2002, William Spencer wrote:

> I'm new here, but me and my son are redoing a 1970 bus.
> 
> Here is my problem. After re-building the engine and putting it in the bus 
> I started to troubleshoot it as to why it backfired and would not run.
> 
> When I took out a spark plug and disconnected the coil I noticed that when 
> the starter turned the engine over there was no pressure coming out of the 
> spark plug hole.  In fact I could detect a suction!!!!!!!!!!!!!
> 
> When I had my son to manually turn the crank counter-clockwise (opposite of 
> what the starter does right?) I then could detect some pressure coming out 
> of the spark plug hole.
> 
> I can remember that I aligned the two dots on one gear with the one dot on 
> the other gear when I mated the camshaft with the crankshaft.
> 
> When I laid the rods and crank into the case did I orient the rods to be at 
> bottom dead center instead of top dead center?
> 
> I think this means I am going to have to pull the engine, crack the case, 
> and reset the crank and rods?  Right?
> 
> Any suggestions?
> 
> My son said we should get a starter that goes counterclockwise, but then 
> the fan would not cool the jugs!?!?!?!?!?!!?!?!!!?
> 
> Oh well, this project is more therapy and fun, so I don't mind the time and 
> cost too much.
> 
> After you finish laughing, any guidance would be appreciated.
